      <title>Possible Apply Poison Bug</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Rogue&amp;message.id=1913#M1913</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;I wanted to get some more opinions before I sent out a bug alert to SOE because there are people out there that know alot more than me.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I have just been learning to make and apply poisons.&amp;nbsp; I'm using a Bloodpoint which doesn't proc for me until lvl 26 (I'm currenly 23).&amp;nbsp; I've successfully applied poison to my blade and according to other rogues I've talked to, the poison is administered like a proc, going off whenever it feels like it when I'm using my weapon (except when I'm backstabbing).&amp;nbsp; And the poison remains on the blade as long as I stay in zone.&amp;nbsp; Here's the problem - I played in Paludual Caverns last night for 3 hours and towards the beginning of that 3 hours I was notified that I had successfully applied the poison to my blade.&amp;nbsp; For all that three hours, not once did I get notice that I was poisoning anything.&amp;nbsp; At first,&amp;nbsp;I thought it was because I was in an uber-group and we were just killing them off too fast but then I basically became tank for a while and still nothing.&amp;nbsp; Do you think it is possible that there might be a bug to my poison proc because my blade itself has a proc that will not go off for another 3 lvls so it bugs the poison not to proc??&amp;nbsp; :smileymad:&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I hope it is a bug that possibly can be fixed because if not it leads to another possible suggestion for SOE from me - If you're going to make Make Poison so friggin expensive it would behoove them to make the poison a teensy bit more useful.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
