      <title>Re: Possible Apply Poison Bug</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Rogue&amp;message.id=1916#M1916</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Ok, that's an old school one.&amp;nbsp; The difference is all poisons prior to PoP were single shot items.&amp;nbsp; You apply them to your blade, and the moment you attack (not backstab, it's gotta be a pierce) they go off and either hit or are resisted.&amp;nbsp; After that your weapon is no longer poisoned, and you have to do it all over again to re-poison your blade.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Look in your log files at the beginning of the first fight after you successfully applied the poison.&amp;nbsp; The lines you are looking for will be found right after the line Autoattack *ON*.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
      <pubDate>Tue, 07 Sep 2004 17:17:23 GMT</pubDate>
