      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The apply poison skill is fairly tedious to work up, but then becomes pointless once you have a single level of poison mastery AA.&amp;nbsp; Part of that AA description reads:&amp;nbsp; 'Once one point is applied to this ability, you will never again fail in poison application.'&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Before the AA came out, I don't recall failing much on applying poisons.&amp;nbsp; It's been a *long* time since I did so, however.&amp;nbsp; I do know that it only applies to old school poisons, that you apply to your weapon.&amp;nbsp; It does not apply to the poisons that you 'cast' and get a proc buff.&lt;/P&gt;</description>
